 When we got to our camp we arriv there at 1 oclock in the morn had a good feed of stew ( a new dish in the armi ) Tea chang my sock took off my drawer turn them insid out put them on again laid down for a bit of a sleep when at 6.30 the same morn we got into motor car to go off to the Somm this was the month of March we travel all that day until 2 pm when we went into Billet for one night next morn we march to a Railway station pass on the way Mont-de-Cat got on the train for Amien from there after ride in cattl Truck ( 8 chevioux or 40 Homm ) about 40 men in each Truck all day , we arriv got into Billet at Gudinett [ ? ] where we onli had one night sleep. then next day at 12.30 we got the order that we were want at onc to pack up straight away be readi to get into car at 1.30 pm so we got into the car went quick right through Amien again to a villag call Darnacourt where we got into Billet as it was rain hard all day we were glad of a bit of shelter . we each got as mani bomb as we could carri extra ammunit Tucker at 8.30 pm the same night start for the front where the Hun had broken through a few day befor . there were troop go in all direct , some come down other go up , all seem in a muddl to my mind . Anyway we arriv at a villag got in a big barn where we stay two night when we got order to move up we were wander about half the night
